Barratt to ‘Move Back Into Profit’ This Year, CEO Tells Sky News

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-01T20:04:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/barratt-to-move-back-into-profit-this-year-ceo-tells-sky-news.html
  Barratt Developments Plc  is poised
to “move back into profit this year,” after seeing margins
double in the first half, Chief Executive Officer Mark Clare
told Sky News in an interview.  The company will “work hard” to bring the share price
back up to a “sensible level” and over the past 18 months has
committed to 800 million pounds ($1.3 billion) worth of land for
future development, Clare said in the interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 